2011-01-14: The Jasmine Revolution in Tunisia led to the ousting of President Zine el-Abidine Ben Ali, ending his 23-year reign and forcing him into exile.
2011-01-28: The Muslim Brotherhood in Egypt urged its followers to protest after Friday prayers, marking the first time in the latest wave of unrest that the group has made such a call.
2013-02-11: Two men charged in the death of a Chicago teen who performed at an inauguration event. Carnival Triumph cruise ship being towed to Mobile, AL after experiencing a fire in the engine room. Speculation arises about the possibility of the next pope being from Africa or Latin America.
